/* QUESTION 2 */
SELECT v.vendor_id, v.name, SUM(t.dinheiroTotal) as total
FROM example as t 
LEFT JOIN vendor as v ON v.vendor_id = t.vendorId
GROUP BY v.vendor_id, v.name
ORDER BY total DESC
LIMIT 3

paragraphs.text:
%sql
/* QUESTION 3 */
SELECT  month(t.date) as month, year(t.date) as year, COUNT(t.id) as total
FROM example as t
INNER JOIN payment as p ON p.payment_type = t.payment_type
WHERE 
    year(t.date) >= (2020 - 4)
    AND p.payment_lookup = 'Cash'
GROUP BY 
    month, year

%sql
/* QUESTION 4 */
SELECT day(t.date) as day, month(t.date) as month, COUNT(t.id) as total /* or SUM(t.gorjeta) */
FROM example as t
WHERE 
    year(t.date) = 2012
    AND month(t.date) >= 10
    AND t.gorjeta > 0
GROUP BY 
    day, month
